 | publisher=[[Wiley-Blackwell]] |year=2002 |isbn=978-0-86542-078-6 |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite journal|first1=Lianxing |last1=Wen|first2=Donald V. |last2=Helmberger |title=Ultra-Low Velocity Zones Near the Core-Mantle Boundary from Broadband PKP Precursors |journal=[[Science (journal)|Science]] |volume=279 |pages=1701\u20131703  |year=1998 |doi=10.1126/science.279.5357.1701 |pmid=9497284|url=http://geophysics.geo.sunysb.edu/wen/Reprints/WenHelmberger98Science.pdf |ref=harv|issue=5357|bibcode = 1998Sci...279.1701W }}\n{{refend}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Seismology}}\n* [http://www.emsc-csem.org/ European-Mediterranean Seismological Center], real-time earthquake information website.\n* [http://www.seismosoc.org/ Seismological Society of America].\n* [http://www.iris.edu/ Incorporated Research Institutions for Seismology].\n* [https://earthquake.usgs.gov/earthquakes/ USGS Earthquake Hazards Program].\n* [https://projects.eri.ucsb.edu/understanding/history.html A brief history of seismology to 1910] (UCSB ERI)\n\n{{Geophysics navbox}}\n{{Geology}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Seismology| ]]\n[[Category:Earthquake engineering| ]]\n", "name_user": "83d40m", "label": "safe", "comment": "needs update of current records during transportation shutdowns --- tbc", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Seismology"}
{"title_page": "1968 2. divisjon", "text_new": "{{Infobox football league season\n| competition        = 2. divisjon\n| season             = 1968\n| winners            = [[IK Start|Start]] (Group A)<br />[[IL H\u00f8dd|H\u00f8dd]] (Group B)\n| promoted           = Start<br />H\u00f8dd\n| relegated          = [[Odds BK|Odd]]<br />[[SK Vard Haugesund|Vard]]<br />[[Steinkjer FK|Steinkjer]]<br />[[SK Gj\u00f8vik-Lyn|Gj\u00f8vik-Lyn]]\n| continentalcup1    = [[1969\u201370 European Cup Winners' Cup|Cup Winners' Cup]]\n| continentalcup1 qualifiers = [[Mj\u00f8ndalen IF|Mj\u00f8ndalen]]\n| continentalcup2    = \n| continentalcup2 qualifiers = \n| matches            = \n| total goals        = \n| league topscorer   = \n| biggest home win   = \n| biggest away win   = \n| highest scoring    = \n<!--\nPLEASE USE THESE PARAMETERS ONLY IF THERE ARE RELIABLE SOURCES FOR THE RESPECTIVE RECORD/STREAK. SINGLE MATCH REPORTS ARE USUALLY NOT SUFFICIENT!\n-->\n| longest wins       = \n| longest winless    = \n| longest unbeaten   = \n| longest losses     = \n| highest attendance = \n| average attendance = \n| prevseason         = [[1967 2. divisjon|1967]]\n| nextseason         = [[1969 2. divisjon|1969]]\n}}\n\nThe '''1968 [[1. divisjon|2. divisjon]]''' was a [[Norway|Norwegian]] second-tier [[association football|football]] league season.\n\nThe league was contested by 16 teams, divided into two groups; A and B.<ref name=\"rsssf\">{{cite web |url=http://www.rsssf.no/1968/Second.html |title=Second division 1968 |first=Lars |last=Aarhus |work=RSSSF Norway |accessdate=30 November 2018}}</ref> The winners of group A and B were promoted to the [[1969 1. divisjon]]. The two lowest placed teams in both groups were relegated to the [[2. divisjon|3. divisjon]].\n\n==Overview==\n===Summary===\n[[IK Start|Start]] won group A with 24 points. [[IL H\u00f8dd|H\u00f8dd]] won group B with 19 points. Both teams were promoted to the 1969 1. divisjon.\n\n==Tables==\n===Group A===\n<onlyinclude>{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WDL\n|section=Group A\n|res_col_header=PQR\n|winpoints=2\n\n|team1=IKS|name_IKS=[[IK Start|Start]]\n|team2=BRY|name_BRY=[[Bryne FK|Bryne]]\n|team3=PRS|name_PRS=[[IF Pors|Pors]]\n|team4=VIG|name_VIG=[[FK Vig\u00f8r|Vig\u00f8r]]\n|team5=EIK|name_EIK=[[Eik-T\u00f8nsberg|Eik]]\n|team6=\u00d8RN|name_\u00d8RN=[[FK \u00d8rn-Horten|\u00d8rn]]\n|team7=ODD|name_ODD=[[Odds BK|Odd]]\n|team8=VRD|name_VRD=[[SK Vard Haugesund|Vard]]\n\n|win_IKS=11|draw_IKS=2|loss_IKS=1|gf_IKS=36|ga_IKS=18|status_IKS=CP\n|win_BRY=9 |draw_BRY=1|loss_BRY=4|gf_BRY=37|ga_BRY=25\n|win_PRS=5 |draw_PRS=5|loss_PRS=4|gf_PRS=21|ga_PRS=19\n|win_VIG=5 |draw_VIG=2|loss_VIG=7|gf_VIG=19|ga_VIG=23\n|win_EIK=4 |draw_EIK=4|loss_EIK=6|gf_EIK=15|ga_EIK=19\n|win_\u00d8RN=4 |draw_\u00d8RN=3|loss_\u00d8RN=7|gf_\u00d8RN=26|ga_\u00d8RN=29\n|win_ODD=4 |draw_ODD=3|loss_ODD=7|gf_ODD=22|ga_ODD=25|status_ODD=R\n|win_VRD=3 |draw_VRD=2|loss_VRD=9|gf_VRD=24|ga_VRD=42|status_VRD=R\n\n|col_PRO=green1|text_PRO=Promotion to [[1969 1. divisjon|1. divisjon]]\n|result1=PRO\n|col_REL=red1 |text_REL=Relegation to [[2. divisjon|3. divisjon]]\n|result7=REL\n|result8=REL\n\n|show_limit=5\n|class_rules=1) points; 2) goal difference; 3) number of goals scored.\n|update=complete\n|source= [http://www.rsssf.no/1968/Second.html rsssf.no]\n}}</onlyinclude>\n===Group B===\n<onlyinclude>{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WDL\n|section=Group B\n|res_col_header=PQR\n|winpoints=2\n\n|team1=H\u00d8D|name_H\u00d8D=[[IL H\u00f8dd|H\u00f8dd]]\n|team2=ALE|name_ALE=[[Aalesunds FK|Aalesund]]\n|team3=HAM|name_HAM=[[Hamarkameratene]]\n|team4=MJ\u00d8|name_MJ\u00d8=[[Mj\u00f8ndalen IF|Mj\u00f8ndalen]]\n|team5=RAU|name_RAU=[[Raufoss Fotball|Raufoss]]\n|team6=AUR|name_AUR=[[Aurskog-Finstadbru SK|Aurskog]]\n|team7=STE|name_STE=[[Steinkjer FK|Steinkjer]]\n|team8=G/L|name_G/L=[[SK Gj\u00f8vik-Lyn|Gj\u00f8vik-Lyn]]\n\n|win_H\u00d8D=7|draw_H\u00d8D=5|loss_H\u00d8D=2|gf_H\u00d8D=22|ga_H\u00d8D=12|status_H\u00d8D=CP\n|win_ALE=8|draw_ALE=2|loss_ALE=4|gf_ALE=27|ga_ALE=15\n|win_HAM=8|draw_HAM=2|loss_HAM=4|gf_HAM=23|ga_HAM=17\n|win_MJ\u00d8=6|draw_MJ\u00d8=4|loss_MJ\u00d8=4|gf_MJ\u00d8=32|ga_MJ\u00d8=18\n|win_RAU=4|draw_RAU=5|loss_RAU=5|gf_RAU=20|ga_RAU=20\n|win_AUR=4|draw_AUR=3|loss_AUR=7|gf_AUR=17|ga_AUR=21\n|win_STE=3|draw_STE=3|loss_STE=8|gf_STE=18|ga_STE=38|status_STE=R\n|win_G/L=1|draw_G/L=6|loss_G/L=7|gf_G/L=20|ga_G/L=38|status_G/L=R\n\n|col_PRO=green1|text_PRO=Promotion to [[1969 1. divisjon|1. divisjon]]\n|result1=PRO\n|col_ECWC1=#FFEBAD|text_ECWC1=Qualification for the [[1969\u201370 European Cup Winners' Cup|Cup Winners' Cup first round]]\n|result4=ECWC1|note_res_ECWC1=As Lyn qualified for the European Cup, their European Cup Winners' Cup place as [[1968 Norwegian Football Cup|Norwegian Cup winners]] defaulted to Mj\u00f8ndalen, the runners-up.\n|col_REL=red1 |text_REL=Relegation to [[2. divisjon|3. divisjon]]\n|result7=REL\n|result8=REL\n\n|show_limit=5\n|class_rules=1) points; 2) goal difference; 3) number of goals scored.\n|update=complete\n|source= [http://www.rsssf.no/1968/Second.html rsssf.no]\n}}</onlyinclude>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{1. divisjon}}\n{{1968 in Norwegian football}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2018}}\n\n[[Category:1. divisjon seasons]]\n[[Category:1968 in Norwegian football]]\n[[Category:1967\u201368 in European second tier association football leagues|Norway]]\n[[Category:1968\u201369 in European second tier association football leagues|Norway]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football league season\n| competition        = 2. divisjon\n| season             = 1968\n| winners            = [[IK Start|Start]] (Group A)<br />[[IL H\u00f8dd|H\u00f8dd]] (Group B)\n| promoted           = Start<br />H\u00f8dd\n| relegated          = [[Odds BK|Odd]]<br />[[SK Vard Haugesund|Vard]]<br />[[Steinkjer FK|Steinkjer]]<br />[[SK Gj\u00f8vik-Lyn|Gj\u00f8vik-Lyn]]\n| continentalcup1    = [[1969\u201370 European Cup Winners' Cup|Cup Winners' Cup]]\n| continentalcup1 qualifiers = [[Mj\u00f8ndalen IF|Mj\u00f8ndalen]]\n| continentalcup2    = \n| continentalcup2 qualifiers = \n| matches            = \n| total goals        = \n| league topscorer   = \n| biggest home win   = \n| biggest away win   = \n| highest scoring    = \n<!--\nPLEASE USE THESE PARAMETERS ONLY IF THERE ARE RELIABLE SOURCES FOR THE RESPECTIVE RECORD/STREAK. SINGLE MATCH REPORTS ARE USUALLY NOT SUFFICIENT!\n-->\n| longest wins       = \n| longest winless    = \n| longest unbeaten   = \n| longest losses     = \n| highest attendance = \n| average attendance = \n| prevseason         = [[1967 2. divisjon|1967]]\n| nextseason         = [[1969 2. divisjon|1969]]\n}}\n\nThe '''1968 [[1. divisjon|2. divisjon]]''' was a [[Norway|Norwegian]] second-tier [[association football|football]] league season.\n\nThe league was contested by 16 teams, divided into two groups; A and B.<ref name=\"rsssf\">{{cite web |url=http://www.rsssf.no/1968/Second.html |title=Second division 1968 |first=Lars |last=Aarhus |work=RSSSF Norway |accessdate=30 November 2018}}</ref> The winners of group A and B were promoted to the [[1969 1. divisjon]]. The two lowest placed teams in both groups were relegated to the [[2. divisjon|3. divisjon]].\n\n==Overview==\n===Summary===\n[[IK Start|Start]] won group A with 24 points. [[IL H\u00f8dd|H\u00f8dd]] won group B with 19 points. Both teams were promoted to the 1969 1. divisjon.\n\n==Tables==\n===Group A===\n<onlyinclude>{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WDL\n|section=Group A\n|res_col_header=PQR\n|winpoints=2\n\n|team1=IKS|name_IKS=[[IK Start|Start]]\n|team2=BRY|name_BRY=[[Bryne FK|Bryne]]\n|team3=PRS|name_PRS=[[IF Pors|Pors]]\n|team4=VIG|name_VIG=[[FK Vig\u00f8r|Vig\u00f8r]]\n|team5=EIK|name_EIK=[[Eik-T\u00f8nsberg|Eik]]\n|team6=\u00d8RN|name_\u00d8RN=[[FK \u00d8rn-Horten|\u00d8rn]]\n|team7=ODD|name_ODD=[[Odds BK|Odd]]\n|team8=VRD|name_VRD=[[SK Vard Haugesund|Vard]]\n\n|win_IKS=11|draw_IKS=2|loss_IKS=1|gf_IKS=36|ga_IKS=18|status_IKS=CP\n|win_BRY=9 |draw_BRY=1|loss_BRY=4|gf_BRY=37|ga