{"title_page": "Allison Williams (reporter)", "text_new": "{{about|the American sportscaster|the American actress|Allison Williams (actress)|the 2003 pageant titleholder|Allison Williams (Miss West Virginia)}}\n{{short description|American sportscaster}}\n{{multiple issues|\n{{BLP primary sources|date=January 2013}}\n{{notability|Biographies|date=January 2013}}\n}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name        = Allison Williams\n| image       = ESPN Sideline Reporter Allison Williams.jpg\n| caption     = Williams at [[Salem Football Stadium]] in December 2012\n| birth_name  = \n| birth_date  = {{Birth date and age|mf=yes|1984|1|18}}\n| birth_place = \n| death_date  = \n| death_place = \n| alma_mater  = [[University of Miami]]\n| occupation  = [[ESPN]] Sideline Reporter \n| years active = 2006-present \n| alias       =\n| title       =\n| family      = \n| spouse      = \n| domestic_partner =\n| children    = \n| relatives   =\n| ethnic      =\n| religion    =\n| salary      =\n| networth    =\n| credits     = \n| agent       =\n| employer    = [[ESPN]]\n| residence   = \n| nationality = American\n| URL         =\n}}\n\n'''Allison Williams''' (born January 18, 1984) is a sportscaster with [[ESPN]] and former host for select pregame/postgame shows for Marlins Live. She did field reporting with play-by-play man [[Rich Waltz]] and color commentator [[Tommy Hutton]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://miami.marlins.mlb.com/mia/schedule/shows_partners.jsp |title=Marlins TV and Radio Shows and Broadcast Partners |work=marlins.com: Schedule |publisher=Miami.marlins.mlb.com |date=2013-05-24 |accessdate=2014-01-07}}</ref>\n\n==Broadcasting career==\nWilliams worked for ''Marlins Live'' for the [[Miami Marlins]] as a sideline reporter and host for pregame and postgame shows. She previously also did reporting for the [[Florida Panthers]] on home games with play-by-play man [[Steve Goldstein (broadcaster)|Steve Goldstein]], Color Analyst [[Bill Lindsay]], and Sportscaster Frank Forte. In addition, Williams also does sideline reporting for telecasts on college football and basketball for the [[ESPN|ESPN Networks]].<ref>{{cite web|author=Fox Sports |url=http://foxsportsflorida.com/pages/landing?blockID=98452 |title=Florida |work=FOX Sports on MSN |publisher=Foxsportsflorida.com |date=2013-12-28 |accessdate=2014-01-07}}</ref>\n\n==Other work==\nIn addition to college football, college basketball, the Panthers, and the Marlins, Williams has hosted shows such as ''Miccosukee Sports Rap'', ''The Jason Taylor Celebrity Golf Special'', ''Ultimate Fan Experience'', and other shows.<ref>{{cite web|author=Fox Sports |url=http://www.foxsportsflorida.com/pages/bios |title=Florida |work=FOX Sports on MSN |publisher=Foxsportsflorida.com |date=2013-12-28 |accessdate=2014-01-07}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nWilliams grew up in [[Michigan]] and graduated from the [[University of Miami]] in 2006 with a degree in broadcast journalism.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thesportsbank.net/sidelineprincesses/espnu-reporter-allison-williams-678/|title=ESPN's Allison Williams is not the actress Allison Williams|date=28 February 2016|publisher=The Sports Bank}}</ref> In her spare time, she enjoys running, going to the beach, doing crosswords, kickboxing, playing softball, and spending time with her family and friends. She loves all sports, but her favorite sports are football, basketball, baseball, and hockey.<ref>{{cite web|author=Fox Sports |url=http://www.foxsportsflorida.com/pages/allison-asks |title=Florida &#124; FOX Sports on MSN |publisher=Foxsportsflorida.com |date=2013-12-28 |accessdate=2014-01-07}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://espnmediazone.com/us/bios/williams_allison/ Williams] at [[ESPN]]\n*{{twitter|AllisonW_Sports}}\n\n{{ESPN}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Williams, Allison}}\n[[Category:1984 births]]\n[[Category:Journalists from Michigan]]\n[[Category:University of Miami alumni]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Miami Marlins broadcasters]]\n[[Category:Florida Panthers broadcasters]]\n[[Category:Place of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:College basketball announcers in the United States]]\n[[Category:National Hockey League broadcasters]]\n[[Category:College football announcers]]\n[[Category:Major League Baseball broadcasters]]\n[[Category:American sports announcers]]\n", "text_old": "}}\n{{about|the American sportscaster|the American actress|Allison Williams (actress)|the 2003 pageant titleholder|Allison Williams (Miss West Virginia)}}\n{{short description|American sportscaster}}\n{{multiple issues|\n{{BLP primary sources|date=January 2013}}\n{{notability|Biographies|date=January 2013}}\n}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name        = Allison Williams\n| image       = ESPN Sideline Reporter Allison Williams.jpg\n| caption     = Williams at [[Salem Football Stadium]] in December 2012\n| birth_name  = \n| birth_date  = {{Birth date and age|mf=yes|1984|1|18}}\n| birth_place = \n| death_date  = \n| death_place = \n| alma_mater  = [[University of Miami]]\n| occupation  = [[ESPN]] Sideline Reporter \n| years active = 2006-present \n| alias       =\n| title       =\n| family      = \n| spouse      = \n| domestic_partner =\n| children    = \n| relatives   =\n| ethnic      =\n| religion    =\n| salary      =\n| networth    =\n| credits     = \n| agent       =\n| employer    = [[ESPN]]\n| residence   = \n| nationality = American\n| URL         =\n}}\n\n'''Allison Williams''' (born January 18, 1984) is a sportscaster with [[ESPN]] and former host for select pregame/postgame shows for Marlins Live. She did field reporting with play-by-play man [[Rich Waltz]] and color commentator [[Tommy Hutton]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://miami.marlins.mlb.com/mia/schedule/shows_partners.jsp |title=Marlins TV and Radio Shows and Broadcast Partners |work=marlins.com: Schedule |publisher=Miami.marlins.mlb.com |date=2013-05-24 |accessdate=2014-01-07}}</ref>\n\n==Broadcasting career==\nWilliams worked for ''Marlins Live'' for the [[Miami Marlins]] as a sideline reporter and host for pregame and postgame shows. She previously also did reporting for the [[Florida Panthers]] on home games with play-by-play man [[Steve Goldstein (broadcaster)|Steve Goldstein]], Color Analyst [[Bill Lindsay]], and Sportscaster Frank Forte. In addition, Williams also does sideline reporting for telecasts on college football and basketball for the [[ESPN|ESPN Networks]].<ref>{{cite web|author=Fox Sports |url=http://foxsportsflorida.com/pages/landing?blockID=98452 |title=Florida |work=FOX Sports on MSN |publisher=Foxsportsflorida.com |date=2013-12-28 |accessdate=2014-01-07}}</ref>\n\n==Other work==\nIn addition to college football, college basketball, the Panthers, and the Marlins, Williams has hosted shows such as ''Miccosukee Sports Rap'', ''The Jason Taylor Celebrity Golf Special'', ''Ultimate Fan Experience'', and other shows.<ref>{{cite web|author=Fox Sports |url=http://www.foxsportsflorida.com/pages/bios |title=Florida |work=FOX Sports on MSN |publisher=Foxsportsflorida.com |date=2013-12-28 |accessdate=2014-01-07}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nWilliams grew up in [[Michigan]] and graduated from the [[University of Miami]] in 2006 with a degree in broadcast journalism.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thesportsbank.net/sidelineprincesses/espnu-reporter-allison-williams-678/|title=ESPN's Allison Williams is not the actress Allison Williams|date=28 February 2016|publisher=The Sports Bank}}</ref> In her spare time, she enjoys running, going to the beach, doing crosswords, kickboxing, playing softball, and spending time with her family and friends. She loves all sports, but her favorite sports are football, basketball, baseball, and hockey.<ref>{{cite web|author=Fox Sports |url=http://www.foxsportsflorida.com/pages/allison-asks |title=Florida &#124; FOX Sports on MSN |publisher=Foxsportsflorida.com |date=2013-12-28 |accessdate=2014-01-07}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External link